.TH DGASM 1 "@CURRENT_DATE@" "v@PROJECT_VERSION@" "DGASM User Manual"
.SH NAME
dgasm \- Assembler for Data General Nova and Eclipse systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dgasm
[\fB\-t\fR \fIcpu\fR] [\fB\-f\fR \fIformat\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIoutput\fR] \fIinput.s\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dgasm
is a cross-assembler designed to target vintage Data General architectures. It supports
various CPU-specific instruction sets and generates output in several formats compatible
with modern simulators (like SIMH) or original hardware.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-t " cpu"
Specify the target CPU architecture. Supported values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBnova1\fR, \fBnova3\fR, \fBnova4\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fBeclipse_s140\fR
.RE
.TP
.BI \-f " format"
Set the output encoding format.
.RS
.IP \fBbinary\fR
Raw machine code bytes.
.IP \fBoctal\fR
A text-based octal representation of the memory image.
.IP \fBeclipse\fR
Format to be pasted into an Eclipse's console monitor, if it has one.
.IP \fBsimh\fR
Format to be pasted into SIMH's monitor.
.RE
.TP
.BI \-o " output"
Specify the name of the output file. If omitted, defaults to \fBstdout\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
Assemble a Nova 3 program for use in SIMH:
.IP
.B dgasm -t nova3 -f simh -o boot.out main.s
.SH BUGS
Report bugs to the project repository at:
.I https://github.com/CWood1/dgasm
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Connor Wood (Venos).
